body: I'm not sure if you resolved this or not but you can only get a named object from a named type. Named objects also have package information. For unnamed types, you'll have to do something different. Also I noticed https://github.com/h4ck3rm1k3/gcc-1/commit/d51d1f90e4955eb61f45a752b0d03ad10644c238#diff-6dfba358043a87274c856db299475389R4071 doesn't seem right to me. ...interface{} isn't the only var args type. Ideally, that would also be "...%s", type->name()
